cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with video frame synthesis using a dual network that can use both dynamic and static convolutional motion kernels. This is a problem that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves training a network to predict future frames. The use of convolutional kernels also suggests that the paper may fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper's focus on developing a robust approach suggests that it may also fall under neural networks (cs.NE).
